Avistei dois adultos e esse filhote no chão.

Percebi que o filhote queria independência, não entendi o motivo.

Como é uma região de muitos gatos domésticos, eu resolvi ficar por ali algum tempo observando.

Com uma vara comprida, consegui com que o filhote se apegasse à essa vara. Então, movimentei a vara até a árvores mais próxima.

Os adultos apresentavam estar muito preocupados, claro, no chão eles são alvos fáceis para os gatos domésticos.

description: This picture is from the 20th of November 2022. I took this photo when I was sitting on the couch in my home and I looked outside and saw this l little animal looking at me. This animal always appears in the garden next to my house and sometimes it gets close to the home and it even goes inside the kitchen to try to steal bananas. It always looks at the people inside the house, but they go away when we get close. It's normal to see them in groups but on this particular occasion, I saw one who was alone. I know this is a black-pencilled marmoset because the picture of the species is exactly what this animal in the picture looks like. I also know this because my parents always say their names in portuguese which is mico or sagui.

description: One of the coolest experiences of my life. They took a little piece of banana from me, but were too wary to take more. They were hanging out on the roofs of the houses here, and you could hear them calling to each other in their high pitched “singing” vocalizations. I spotted at least 3 individuals for certain, though there were more than that. They approached when I mimicked their singing by whistling in a similar way, and when they saw my banana (“banana prata” is the cultivar). You can hear them singing to each other every single day in this area, and in the nearby roads there are “animal crossing” signs, with man-made rope bridges connecting the tops of the trees to each other, to help the marmosets cross without having to risk being hit by cars when crossing the road.
